    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine and a tactile 6-speed manual transmission. This example remains a driver\u2019s favorite, benefiting from a documented VANOS system overhaul and proactive rear subframe reinforcement to maintain chassis rigidity. The powertrain delivers linear acceleration through individual throttle bodies, while the factory limited-slip differential ensures precise power delivery out of corners. The suspension remains tight, providing the communicative feedback characteristic of the M-division's peak analog era. While showing minor signs of honest use consistent with its mileage, the car is structurally sound and free of typical cooling system vulnerabilities. A turn-key performance icon for the serious enthusiast.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 46
    },
    {
